Consider two point sources $s_1$ and $s_2$, as shown in Fig. 15.10, which emit coherent waves. Show that curves such as that traced by point $p$, for which the phase difference for rays $r_1$ and $r_2$ is a constant, are hyperboloids in three dimensions.

